data.chText: 使烦恼（尤指不断重复的事情）
data.enText: to annoy sb, especially by sth you continuously do or by sth that continuously happens

data.chText: 她故意操那种口音的样子实在令我恼火。
data.enText: The way she puts on that accent really irritates me.
to make your skin or a part of your body sore or painful

data.chText: 有些药物会刺激胃内壁。
data.enText: Some drugs can irritate the lining of the stomach.

data.chText: 我觉得她极其令人恼火。
令人痛苦的咳嗽 / 皮疹
他指出那封信还没有发出去，有点生气的样子。
data.enText: He noted, with some irritation, that the letter had not been sent.

simple_means.memory_skill: ir 表加强 + rit 擦 + ate 表动词 → 摩擦 → 激怒

means: 使烦恼(尤指不断重复的事情)

ex.chText: 如果不是被惹恼了，他是不会责骂你的。
ex.enText: He would not have scolded you if he hadn't been provoked.

ex.chText: 保罗坚持说他是因为被激怒才打架的。
ex.enText: Paul insisted that he was provoked into fighting.

synonyms.bx: 尤指故意激怒某人，含有挑衅之意。

ex.chText: 最让她生气的是他居然一句道歉的话都没有。
ex.enText: What angered her most was his total lack of apology.

ex.chText: 老师对他的谎话感到愤怒。
ex.enText: The teacher was angered by his lies.

synonyms.bx: 指激怒某人，其程度通常高于 annoy。

ex.chText: 他翻来覆去的发问让她非常生气。
ex.enText: She was annoyed by his repeated questions.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，程度较轻，强调不断地烦扰，尤指以重复性的行为让人心烦或恼火。

ex.chText: 请不要问些傻问题来烦我。
ex.enText: Don't badger me with your silly questions.

synonyms.bx: 强调没完没了的发问、噪音等惹人生气。

ex.enText: She is very busy; please don't bother her.

ex.chText: 对不起打扰你一下，到火车站怎么走？
ex.enText: I'm sorry to bother you, can you tell me the way to the station?

synonyms.bx: 主要侧重于动作、客观事物对人的搅扰，而不强调人的心理及思维方面。

ex.chText: 外面的嘈杂声让我睡不好觉。
ex.enText: The noise outside disturbed my sleep.

synonyms.bx: 常指打断他人的睡眠、工作等，语气较强。

ex.enText: The reporters wouldn't stop hounding him.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为获得某种东西（如信息、隐情等）而不停地追着骚扰某人。

ex.chText: 他周末总是中午才起床，真让我恼火。
ex.enText: It really irritates me when he gets up at noon at weekends.

synonyms.bx: 指因重复或长时间做某事而使人不快。

ex.chText: 妻子没完没了的抱怨真让他烦恼不已。
ex.enText: He was pestered with complaints from his wife.

synonyms.bx: 尤指不断地要求某人做某事，强调纠缠至其难以忍受的地步。

tr: excite to an abnormal condition, or chafe or inflame
excite to some characteristic action or condition, such as motion, contraction, or nervous impulse, by the application of a stimulus
example: irritate the glands of a leaf
Mosquitoes buzzing in my ear really bothers me
It irritates me that she never closes the door after she leaves

value.def: If something irritates you, it keeps annoying you.

example.ex: Perhaps they were irritated by the sound of crying.
example.tran: 也许他们被哭声惹烦了。

example.ex: Not surprisingly, her teacher is getting irritated with her.
example.tran: 毫不奇怪,她的老师有点被她惹恼了。

value.def: If something irritates a part of your body, it causes it to itch or become sore.

example.ex: Wear rubber gloves while chopping chillies as they can irritate the skin.
example.tran: 切辣椒时要戴橡胶手套,因为辣椒会刺激皮肤。

value.tran: 刺激(身体部位);使发痒;使疼痛
